Big Spring Refinery-Community Relations








	Big Spring, Texas

	Alon and the Big Spring Refinery employees are active in the community, schools, and local charitable organizations.  Alon’s commitment to education has enabled the Big Spring School District to build the Alon Technology Center where teachers and students receive training and conduct workshops.  Our refinery has also been awarded the Employer Excellence Award from the Texas Workforce Development Board for being an exemplary employer and for contributions toward local development and corporate citizenship. We support numerous local charitable organizations and community events, such as:

Alon USA and ALON Brands Funtastic Fourth

Big Spring Cowboy Reunion and Rodeo

Big Spring ISD, Forsan ISD and Coahoma ISD

Boys and Girls Club of Big Spring

Big Spring State Hospital

Howard College

Heritage Museum

Pops in the Park

Relay for Life

Salvation Army Angel Tree Program

United Way of Big Spring and Howard County

U.S. National Hang Gliding Competition

West Texas Centers Hoops, Dreams and Goals 

	These are only a few of the important causes that Alon and the refinery employees support in Big Spring and Howard County.  We are proud to live in and be a part of the West Texas community.


 













