Alon USA Energy Inc., headquartered in Dallas, TX engages in the refinement and marketing of petroleum products in the southwestern United States. The company also operates through Southwest Convenience Stores, a wholly owned subsidiary which operates as a regional licensee… MoreAlon USA Energy Inc., headquartered in Dallas, TX engages in the refinement and marketing of petroleum products in the southwestern United States. The company also operates through Southwest Convenience Stores, a wholly owned subsidiary which operates as a regional licensee of more than three hundred 7-Eleven stores in the southwest.
• Delek US Holdings Inc. completed the acquisition of a 48% share of Alon USA Energy Inc. in May, 2015.

The IT department at Alon USA focuses on the support and deployment of the company's supply chain and retail technology platform.… More• Delek US Holdings Inc. completed the acquisition of a 48% share of Alon USA Energy Inc. in May, 2015.

The IT department at Alon USA focuses on the support and deployment of the company's supply chain and retail technology platform. The company utilizes a JD Edwards-based platform for its financial application and ERP needs. A Director of Marketing Technology focuses on the organization's point-of-sale, marketing, and other mobile retail technologies. 

Operating with a degree of autonomy is a small IT support group for Alon's wholly owned subsidiary, Southwest Convenience Stores. This business unit IT group provides retail technology and IT support for the company's Odessa-based corporate office and retail locations.





